cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a meta-learning framework that automatically extracts cross-task relations and constructs a meta-knowledge graph. This involves learning from previous tasks and transferring knowledge to new ones. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): Meta-learning is a subfield of machine learning that focuses on learning to learn. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Meta-learning is also relevant to artificial intelligence, as it aims to improve the efficiency of learning new tasks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper evaluates the proposed framework on few-shot image classification, which is a computer vision task. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper mentions the interpretability of the model, which is a topic of interest in natural language processing. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The proposed framework likely involves the use of neural networks, which falls under this sub-category.
